  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty in boundary conditions and blood rheology is discussed throughout the assessment narrative; variability in donor hematocrit and viscosity is acknowledged as a source of aleatory spread. However, not all validation comparisons carry a formal UQ artifact — the RH-index sweep results are reported with prose commentary on scatter rather than a linked quantification node.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-cfd-hemolysis-worst-case",
