      "rationale": "RH index is the primary regulatory QoI for CPB hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Wall shear stress and exposure time are intermediate QoIs feeding the hemolysis model. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis confirms RH index sensitivity to impeller tip speed (dominant) and gap clearance (secondary). QoIs are clinically relevant and well-defined."
